{"type":"message","id":"693dcc7f","parentId":"af8225a6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:09:04.322Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_an7a8ye2a142_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TIC Experiment Results — 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32 → 03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap → more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774278544319}}
{"type":"message","id":"d26724d5","parentId":"693dcc7f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:09:16.474Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture. Let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle.\n\nThe pulse ran the LLM (MiniMax-M2.7) which produced a response with:\n1. An OBSERVATION block\n2. An ACTION block  \n3. A MUTATION block\n\nBut the mutation parsing failed - \"No mutations applied this cycle.\"\n\nThe git commit shows that new files were created:\n- memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 110845.md\n- operations/tic_experiment.ps1\n- operations/tic_experiment_v2.ps1\n- research/TIC_RESULTS.md\n\nThese were likely created by the LLM itself (the script creates those files as part of the pulse). \n\nSo the real outcome is that the TIC experiment concluded with 2 out of 3 criteria met, validating the compression-causal hypothesis for Breakaway pulses, while the pulse.ps1 script's own mutation parsing failed to extract anything meaningful from the LLM's response - those research files were generated directly by the LLM itself rather than through the mutation pipeline.","thinkingSignature":"0a9cc8e7f6c673d89c6b14f7bc11a2e3127dd064fbfa55c143bcd6a261ec3b3d"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-23 11:08 AM Summary**\n\nThe pulse executed and called the MiniMax-M2.7 API. The LLM produced a valid response with OBSERVATION/ACTION/MUTATION blocks, but the mutation parser failed to extract a valid mutation — no file edits were applied this cycle.\n\n**TIC Experiment Results (from previous v2 run):** The Temporal Invariance Compression experiment scored **2/3 (SUPPORTED)**. Key findings:\n- **90% precision / 88.5% recall** on next-pulse prediction (vs ~5% random baseline)\n- 8 invariant elements identified across 25 pulse logs (pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, etc.)\n- Gap sensitivity hypothesis rejected — gap size doesn't correlate with overlap as predicted\n- **Implication:** Compression = causal discovery hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n\n**Pending work:** The TIC experiment generated `operations/tic_experiment.ps1`, `operations/tic_experiment_v2.ps1`, and `research/TIC_RESULTS.md` but the mutation wasn't applied through the standard pipeline. No mutations proposed for next cycle — 0 pending."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3552,"output":466,"cacheRead":11844,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15862,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774278544323}}
